"We are very close to returning to the Pacific Ocean," he promised at the end of August.
However, some analysts believe that the court is unlikely to decide in favor of Bolivia and that even if it did, not much would change.
The UN body in the Netherlands does not have the power to give thousands of territories and has made it clear that it will not determine the outcome of possible discussions.
