New postponement for Germany's new warship
The new frigate of the German Navy should have been put on duty in 2014 to replace the aged warships of the Cold War era, but it will not be received by at least the following year, due to faulty systems and rising costs, they report local media.
The entry into service of the frigate Rheinland-Pfalz, the flagship of the brand new Baden-Wuerttemberg class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, which invokes a representative of the armed forces.
